Gibson Achonu, Owerri Imo State Governor Hope Uzodinma on Wednesday  sent a list of 22 commissioner nominees to the  House of Assembly for screening. The list contains mostly the names of  lawmakers and appointees who served in the previous administrations. The Speaker, Collins Chiji, named those on the list as  Dr  Osunkwo, Iyke Njoku, Prof. V. E. O. Ikegwuoha,  Francis Dibiagwu, Doris Akubuo, Dan Oguh, Noble Atulegwu, C. C. Osuala, Lambert Orisakwe, Obiageri Ajoku, Nkechi Ugwu, Simeon Ibegbulem, Kingsley Ononuju and Declan Emelumba. Others are  Enyinnaya Onuegbu, Rex Anunobi, Raph Nwosu, Fabian Ihekwueme, Tony Umezuruike, Iyke Umeh, Mathias Emejuonu and Love Ineh. After announcing the names, the   Speaker set up an ad hoc committee  headed by Obinna Okwara to  screen the nominees. He  urged the  commissioner designates  to submit all necessary documents that would  help the committee in their job. Copyright PUNCH.
